dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation and Development. Division of Geology and Waters. Atlas Sheet 32 (1923) New Jersey Geological Survey. Relief shown by 10 ft. contour interval and spot heights. Depths shown by soundings in feet at low tide. Title is not given. Region covered: southern Burlington County. Original survey, 1886, principal features revised 1903, 1922. Original survey and revisions to 1908 made under direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer. Revision of 1922 by L. P. Plummer, Topographic Engineer.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1923.
